---
title: Chicken & Cheesy Cauliflower-Rice Bowls with Roasted Carrots & Spicy Crema
description: This wonderfully comforting and savory bowl starts with a twist: wholesome cauliflower rice that’s roasted to a nutty, golden finish, then combined with scallions, melty Monterey Jack cheese, and sour cream for an easy, cheesy riff on risotto. You’ll nestle perfectly seasoned and seared chicken cutlets on top with a drizzle of spicy crema, and serve with simple roasted carrots on the side.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64b69dca58f85793eaa6dc06-28f13781.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64b69dca58f85793eaa6dc06.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-cheesy-cauliflower-rice-bowls-64b69dca58f85793eaa6dc06
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 520 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 28 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 570 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ¼-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

In a #small bowl{}, combine half the @sour cream{3%tablespoon} and as much @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Toss carrots on one side of #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes}.

Once carrots have roasted 5 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully toss @Riced Cauliflower{6%ounce} on empty side of sheet with a drizzle of oil, remaining Fry Seasoning, salt, and pepper. Roast until veggies are browned and tender, about ~{10%minutes} more.

> If cauliflower rice is done before carrots, transfer to a plate and continue roasting carrots up to 5 minutes more. For 4 servings, leave carrots roasting; toss cauliflower rice on a separate baking sheet and roast on middle rack.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; place between 2 large pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until chicken is about ½ inch thick. Season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

> Tent chicken with foil to keep warm.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant and tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in roasted cauliflower rice, @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, remaining sour cream, and @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Remove from heat.

> If mixture seems too thick, stir in water 1 TBSP at a time until desired consistency is reached.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide cheesy cauliflower rice between shallow #bowls{}; top with chicken and carrots in separate sections. Drizzle everything with spicy crema and garnish with scallion greens. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.